 The true indicia of salami are (1) its single non-recurring character and (2) payment prior to the creation of the tenancy. It is the consideration paid by the tenant for being let into possession and can be neither rent nor revenue but is a capital receipt in the hands of the landlord.
 Kamakshya Narain Singh v. The Commissioner of Income Tax (1943) L.R. 70 I.A. 180, relied on.
